README.rst
     1Рєњ====================================================
     2Рєњpluggy - A minimalist production ready plugin system
     3Рєњ====================================================
     4Рєњ
     5Рєњ|pypi| |conda-forge| |versions| |github-actions| |gitter| |black| |codecov|
     6Рєњ
     7РєњThis is the core framework used by the `pytest`_, `tox`_, and `devpi`_ projects.
     8Рєњ
     9РєњPlease `read the docs`_ to learn more!
    10Рєњ
    11РєњA definitive example
    12Рєњ====================
    13Рєњ.. code-block:: python
    14Рєњ
    15Рєњ    import pluggy
    16Рєњ
    17Рєњ    hookspec = pluggy.HookspecMarker("myproject")
    18Рєњ    hookimpl = pluggy.HookimplMarker("myproject")
    19Рєњ
    20Рєњ
    21Рєњ    class MySpec:
    22Рєњ        """A hook specification namespace."""
    23Рєњ
    24Рєњ        @hookspec
    25Рєњ        def myhook(self, arg1, arg2):
    26Рєњ            """My special little hook that you can customize."""
    27Рєњ
    28Рєњ
    29Рєњ    class Plugin_1:
    30Рєњ        """A hook implementation namespace."""
    31Рєњ
    32Рєњ        @hookimpl
    33Рєњ        def myhook(self, arg1, arg2):
    34Рєњ            print("inside Plugin_1.myhook()")
    35Рєњ            return arg1 + arg2
    36Рєњ
    37Рєњ
    38Рєњ    class Plugin_2:
    39Рєњ        """A 2nd hook implementation namespace."""
    40Рєњ
    41Рєњ        @hookimpl
    42Рєњ        def myhook(self, arg1, arg2):
    43Рєњ            print("inside Plugin_2.myhook()")
    44Рєњ            return arg1 - arg2
    45Рєњ
    46Рєњ
    47Рєњ    # create a manager and add the spec
    48Рєњ    pm = pluggy.PluginManager("myproject")
    49Рєњ    pm.add_hookspecs(MySpec)
    50Рєњ
    51Рєњ    # register plugins
    52Рєњ    pm.register(Plugin_1())
    53Рєњ    pm.register(Plugin_2())
    54Рєњ
    55Рєњ    # call our ``myhook`` hook
    56Рєњ    results = pm.hook.myhook(arg1=1, arg2=2)
    57Рєњ    print(results)
    58Рєњ
    59Рєњ
    60РєњRunning this directly gets us::
    61Рєњ
    62Рєњ    $ python docs/examples/toy-example.py
    63Рєњ    inside Plugin_2.myhook()
    64Рєњ    inside Plugin_1.myhook()
    65Рєњ    [-1, 3]
    66Рєњ
    67Рєњ
    68Рєњ.. badges
